Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @onion{1} into thin slices; mince a few slices until you have about 2 tablespoons (4 tablespoons for 4 servings). Zest and quarter @lime{1}. Grate @garlic{1%clove}. Halve @potato buns{2}.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{4%tsp}, half the @smoked paprika{1%tsp}, and a big pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on middle rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, melt @butter{2%tbsp} in a #medium pan{} over medium heat. Add sliced onion, @sugar{1/4%tsp}, and salt. Cook, stirring, until browned and softened, ~{10-15%minutes}. If onion starts to burn, lower heat and add a splash of water.

Stir in a squeeze of lime juice and @Sriracha{1%tsp} to taste.

While onion cooks, in a #large bowl{}, combine @ground beef{10%ounce}, minced onion, half the garlic, remaining paprika, @sugar{1/2%tsp}, and salt. Form into two patties (four for 4), each slightly wider than a burger bun.

Heat a large drizzle of olive oil in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add patties and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-7%minutes} per side.

In the last ~{1-2%minutes} of cooking, top each patty with @gouda cheese{2%slices}; cover pan until cheese melts. Remove from pan and set aside.

> Swap in pork for beef if preferred. Cook patties to desired doneness, 3-5 minutes per side.

Toast buns until golden. For a deeper flavor, toast in pan used for patties over medium heat.

While buns toast, in a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}, @sour cream{1.5%tbsp}, and a squeeze of lime juice. Stir in as much lime zest and remaining garlic as you like. Season with salt and pepper.

Spread as much sauce as you like onto bottom buns; fill buns with patties and Sriracha onion. Divide burgers and potato wedges between plates. Serve with any remaining sauce for dipping and lime wedges on the side.

> Ground beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.